Author: nusantarageneral
Content:
A man obsessed with trains, stole one and crashed it. At his trial, he was sentenced to death by electrocution. His last meal was a banana. They strapped him onto the electric chair, however it didn't turn on. By law, he's set free.

The next day, he stole a train again and crashed it. He was put to trial and sentenced to death again. He requested a banana again for his last meal. But when he was already strapped on the electric chair, nothing happens. Again, they set him free.

He did it again for the third time, however they refused his banana request. Instead, they gave him steak. On the execution day, they turned on the switch... nothing happens.
"Did you give him a BANANA INSTEAD?" yelled one of the guards.
"No, sir!"

Turns out, the banana had nothing to do with him and they set him free again.
### He was really a bad conductor.
